Lambert Hollonius of Licge (†a. 25 May 1522: Lond. xxix. 11, LB. i. 343) went to Basle in Oct. 1518 with Menard of Hom-n (p. 421). As corrector to Froben he proved inefficient (1. 15 n.). He afterwards went on to Italy to study theology‚ and died at Rome. His nephew, Gregory Holonius‚ in the preface to Laurentia&

Antwerp, J. Beller, 6 June 1556, speaks of him as learned in Greek and Hebrew as well as Latin. See BN.]
